(1769, 584, 'Admin', 'hi Ivan, <br />\r\n<br />\r\nYes, I would be interested in a payment method in Russia, we have a big portion of our users from Russia and struggle with paypal. I visited your website, but it seems to be in russian, I would be interested to find more about the solution and cost associated with the service, and how it works. <br />\r\n<br />\r\nThank you<br />\n<br />\nSincerely,<br />\r\n<br />\r\nPanda CashBack Support<br />\r\n<a href=\"http://www.pandacashback.com\">www.pandacashback.com</a><br />\n', '2015-07-14 22:54:36', '', 1, NULL, '1'),
(1770, 584, 'Ivan Domrachev', 'Hi,<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThank you for the quick response. There is an EN button in the upper corners of both <a href=\"http://www.moneta.ru\">www.moneta.ru</a> and <a href=\"http://www.payanyway.ru\">www.payanyway.ru</a> – it should work. However, both websites are going through major update right now, so if something is still wrong with translation, don’t be surprised. Moneta is our own e-wallet and PayAnyWay is our merchant portal.  <br />\r\n<br />\r\nWithdrawals:<br />\r\n•    Bank cards issued by Russian banks - 1%  ($1 min), CIS banks – 2% ($4 min)<br />\r\n•    Yandex e-wallet – 1%<br />\r\n•    QIWI e-wallets - 1.2% <br />\r\n•    Moneta e-wallet - 0%<br />\r\n•    Money transfers CONTACT – 2% <br />\r\n•    Russian and CIS mobile operators - 1%<br />\r\n<br />\r\nNo other fees. Your settlement transfer to your account in our system and its maintenance is free. <br />\r\n<br />\r\nQuick points:<br />\r\n•  All methods besides CONTACT Money transfers are instant. <br />\r\n•  Interaction through API, customer always stays in your interface during withdrawal. <br />\r\n•  Settlement to us in any currency (e.g. USD, Euro, Pounds) but customers receive payouts in rubles (we handle FX). The only exception – Moneta e-wallet – where customers can choose to receive money in foreign currency.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nSo, it’s a brief intro on fees and how it works. The main idea of the service is to let Russian customers receive money to the e-wallets that they traditionally use in Russia or directly to cards without having to set up an account with another payment service like PayPal. Besides that, money received to traditional Russian e-wallets are more immediately available compared to PayPal. <br />\r\n<br />\r\nI will be looking forward to hearing from you. Thank you,<br />\r\nIvan', '2015-07-15 13:59:41', '', 0, NULL, '0'),
