(2055, 720, 'Admin', 'hi Dave, <br />\r\n<br />\r\nFor a starter, i would like to explain the 20% is off the fee not the total sale ( whatever fee eBay charge the seller, we would give 20% of that to the user ), that would translate to roughly $4 in the general category.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nAs far as the communication, the target of the pilot was to evaluate our website as a marketing channel for the program. When we work with an advertiser our email marketing is considered a different marketing channel in which advertisers as big as eBay and Amazon tend to go into the details of is it an approved marketing channel or not and if they want us to run the campaign through it. In this case we didn\'t get the chance to approve it considering that the campaign ran only for 2 weeks period.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWe have tried our best to feature eBay on every place on our website including our home page, our featured page and even as the retailer of the week twice in the same month. <br />\r\n<br />\r\nI looked into your account to offer you a bonus but since no transaction has taken place, i can offer you a bonus the next time you make a purchase through Panda CashBack. <br />\r\n<br />\r\nWe encourage our members to always check the site before buying mainly because our retailers can be sometimes variable, visiting us more often guarantee getting the most out of it. <br />\r\n<br />\r\nLet me know if you have any other question.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThank you<br />\n<br />\nSincerely,<br />\r\n<br />\r\nPanda CashBack Support<br />\r\n<a href=\"http://www.pandacashback.com\">www.pandacashback.com</a><br />\n', '2016-05-21 19:41:03', '', 1, NULL, '1'),
