(72, '7Z8-HDR-GQXR', 'Logan Wise', 'locowise@gmail.com', 1, '2', 'IRS Form W9', 'Hello,<br />\r\n<br />\r\nI received an email stating that I am required to submit IRS Form W9 because I have earned over $600 cashback for 2013. However, the $600+ was earned for rebates on spending which is tax exempt according to the IRS publication 17 chapter 12 section entitled &quot;Cash rebates.&quot; Please review the link below or page 9 of the attached PDF.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<a href=\"http://www.irs.gov/publications/p17/ch12.html#en_US_2012_publink1000172062\">www.irs.gov/publications/p17/ch12.html</a><br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe cashback serves as a basis for reducing the purchase price rather than income. An example is included in the IRS publication referenced above. Furthermore, I am also a member of ebates, Bigcrumbs, Upromise, Capital One Spark Cash Rewards, etc. and none of these companies require a W9.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nTo file a W9 and receive a 1099 would create confusion with the IRS by miscategorizing the cashback as income.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nPlease advise. Thank you.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\nBest regards,<br />\r\nLogan Wise', '2013-04-28 21:32:12', '2013-05-08 22:10:31', '65.191.181.214', NULL, '3', 1, '01:11:07', '1', 1, '0', '0', '83#Publication-17-2012-Your-Federal-Income-Tax.pdf,', '', '<li class=\"smaller\">On 2013-04-28 22:32:12 submitted by Logan Wise</li><li class=\"smaller\">On 2013-04-29 22:13:48 assigned to Admin (Admin) by Admin (Admin)</li><li class=\"smaller\">On 2013-05-08 18:10:31 closed by Admin (Admin)</li>', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
